execute()

execute(string  $controllerMethod, array  $args = array()) : string

Execute a module controller/method.

This is useful for widgetize, modular process.

To check that is this a module execute, use $_SERVER['RUNDIZBONES_MODULEEXECUTE'].
Example:

if (!isset($_SERVER['RUNDIZBONES_MODULEEXECUTE']) || (isset($_SERVER['RUNDIZBONES_MODULEEXECUTE']) && $_SERVER['RUNDIZBONES_MODULEEXECUTE'] !== 'true')) {
    // this is NOT module execute.
} else {
    // this is module execute.
}

Before call this method:
Make sure that the module you specified is enabled otherwise the autoload will not working.

Parameters

string $controllerMethod

The module's controller:method. The class name and its method should not has suffix. Example: Rdb\Modules\MyModule\Controllers\MyPage:index will be automatically converted to Rdb\Modules\MyModule\Controllers\MyPageController:indexAction.
array $args

The arguments of controller's method.

Throws

\InvalidArgumentException

Throw invalid argument exception if controller:method format is invalid.

Returns

string —

Return response content of controller:method.

Inherited from
\Rdb\System\Modules

Tags

None found
